25/* We use one big table for the mapping. We know that the first byte
26 is in range 0x21 to 0xea. The second byte never is in the ranges
27 0x00 to 0x20 and 0x7f to 0xff. Compacting the table by excluding
28 these ranges we get a table with only this gaps:
29
30 at 0x222e 0x2241 0x2250 0x226a 0x2279 0x2321 0x2339 0x235a
31 len 12 9 12 8 5 15 8 7
32
33 at 0x237a 0x2473 0x2576 0x2638 0x2658 0x2741 0x2771 0x2840
34 len 4 11 8 9 38 16 13 62
35
36 at 0x4f53
37 len 43
38
39 It's not worth trying to use these gaps. The table can be generated
40 using
41
42 egrep '^0x' < .../eastasia/jis/jis0208.txt |
43 perl tab.pl
44
45 with tab.pl containing:
46 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
47 $n=0;
48 while (<>) {
49 local($sjis, $jis, $ucs4, %rest) = split;
50 local($u)=hex($ucs4);
51 local($s)=hex($jis);
52 printf ("\n ") if ($n % 4 eq 0);
53 ++$n;
54 printf (" [0x%04x] = 0x%04x,",
55 int(($s - 0x2121) / 256) * 94 + (($s - 0x2121) & 0xff), $u);
56 }
57 printf ("\n");
58 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
59*/

1867/* The mapping of all the other UCS values is quite difficult since they
1868 are distributed from 0x2010 upto to 0xffe5. There are many gaps with
1869 unpredictable place and size. Therefore we use a table which maps
1870 ranges to idexes in a table. This table ca be generated with:
1871
1872 egrep '^0x' < .../eastasia/jis/jis0208.txt | awk '{ print $3, $2}' |
1873 egrep '^0x[^01]' | sort -u | perl tab.pl
1874
1875 where tab.pl is
1876
1877 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1878 $first=$last=$idx=0;
1879 while (<>) {
1880 local($ucs,$jis,%rest) = split;
1881 local($u)=hex($ucs);
1882 if ($u - $last > 6) {
1883 if ($last != 0) {
1884 printf (" { .start = %#06x, .end = %#06x, .idx = %5d },\n",
1885 $first, $last, $idx);
1886 $idx += $last - $first + 1;
1887 }
1888 $first=$u;
1889 }
1890 $last=$u;
1891 }
1892 printf (" { .start = %#06x, .end = %#06x, .idx = %5d }\n",
1893 $first, $last, $idx);
1894 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
1895*/
